    Page: 112
By: Sri Ramakrishna
Tags:
  - Sacrifice-Death=Illusion=The Consummation of Desire
Commentary: This recalls exactly Plato's image of the prisoners in the cave
  (Republic, 514 f.).
---
These people are like ... a frog living in a well, who has never seen the
outside world. He knows only his well; so he will not believe that there is
such a thing as the world. Likewise, people talk so much about the world
because they have not known the joy of God.
